        <h2 id="myths" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Copyright Myths Debunked</h2>
        <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Myth: "If I Give Credit, I Can Use Any Music"</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><strong>False.</strong> Attribution doesn't grant permission. You still need a license.</p>
        <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Myth: "Using Only 30 Seconds Is Legal"</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><strong>False.</strong> There's no "30-second rule." Using even 5 seconds can be infringement.</p>
        <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Myth: "Fair Use Lets Me Use Music in My Video"</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><strong>Mostly false.</strong> Fair use is complex and narrow. Simply using music as background is not fair use.</p>
